    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 16, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 Hormuz added ship drama to the spreadsheet\n\nThe strait is now doing maritime crisis management one hull at a time, because energy chokepoints apparently needed more paperwork.\n\n- **The seizure:** AP says a ship anchored 38 nautical miles northeast of Fujairah was taken by unauthorized personnel and headed toward Iranian waters.\n- **The sinking:** an Indian-flagged cargo ship, the Haji Ali, sank near Oman after an attack sparked a fire; all 14 Indian crew members were rescued.\n- **The diplomacy:** Reuters says China told U.S. officials it wants Hormuz reopened without tolls, curbs or military control.\n\n*The shipping lane remains open in the theoretical sense favored by diplomats and insurance lawyers.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP via Yahoo News](https://malaysia.news.yahoo.com/ship-reported-seized-off-coast-073349851.html) | [Reuters via Yahoo News](https://malaysia.news.yahoo.com/china-wants-strait-hormuz-open-003200596.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🧯 Israel and Lebanon bought 45 more days\n\nThe ceasefire has been extended, which is diplomatic progress and also an admission that the previous timer was making everyone sweat.\n\n- **The extension:** Reuters reports Israel and Lebanon agreed to add 45 days to the April 16 cessation of hostilities after two days of U.S.-facilitated talks in Washington.\n- **The next rooms:** a security track is due at the Pentagon on May 29, with political talks back at the State Department on June 2-3.\n- **The reality check:** AP notes the truce remains shaky, with strikes continuing and Lebanon reporting nearly 40 wounded near Tyre on Friday.\n\n*Peace process, now with calendar invites and live fire in the margins.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via MarketScreener](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/israel-and-lebanon-agree-to-extend-ceasefire-by-45-days-us-state-dept-says-ce7f5bd3d88ef52c) | [AP via WGAL](https://www.wgal.com/article/israel-lebanon-ceasefire-extension/71320402)\n\n---\n\n## 🛰️ Sudan's war found the drone ceiling\n\nSudan's civil war has discovered the grim efficiency layer: cheap aircraft, distant sponsors and civilians under the flight path.\n\n- **The toll:** AP cites U.N. human rights chief Volker Türk saying armed drones are now causing more than 80% of conflict-related civilian deaths in Sudan.\n- **The numbers:** drones killed at least 880 civilians between January and April, while the wider war has killed at least 59,000 and displaced about 13 million.\n- **The escalation:** AP says the RSF recently hit Khartoum airport and nearby areas, while Sudan has accused Ethiopia and the UAE of links to drone attacks.\n\n*The proxy war has upgraded its delivery mechanism. The civilians did not get a vote.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/1c0301faa15f5b57df9621a4b44aa939) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://m.investing.com/news/world-news/un-warns-drone-attacks-drive-surge-in-civilian-deaths-in-sudan-4675307?ampMode=1)"
  }
]
